# Restaurant Agent environment.

# OpenTable Affiliate / Partner API credentials.
#
# Left unset on purpose — the Mock-First scaffold runs entirely off an
# in-memory catalog (see lib/opentable-stub.ts) so you can exercise the
# whole reservation loop (search → availability → reserve → cancel)
# without partner approval. When affiliate access lands, set:
#
#   OPENTABLE_PARTNER_ID=
#   OPENTABLE_API_KEY=
#
# and add a sibling lib/opentable-real.ts that matches the stub's exports.
# The façade in lib/opentable.ts will route the live calls through when
# both env vars are present. Same pattern the Flight Agent uses for
# Duffel (lib/duffel-stub.ts + lib/duffel-real.ts).

# Public base URL this agent is reachable at. The shell's registry uses
# this to discover /.well-known/agent.json + /openapi.json + /api/health,
# and it gets baked into the manifest so downstream consumers can link
# back.
#
# Dev:      http://localhost:3003
# Vercel:   https://<your-restaurant-project>.vercel.app
# Prod DNS: https://restaurant.agents.lumo.rentals
#
# NOTE: do NOT use Vercel's auto-injected VERCEL_URL — that's the per-deploy
# preview URL, not the stable public one. Pin the production URL explicitly.
PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3003
